@startuml brightness_call_tree
' Revised 2026-05-13: applied audit_23/H-03/H-05/H-11/H-12 amendments
!include dark-theme.puml
title Brightness change - full call tree (input sources -> MonitorService -> DDC/VCP)

actor User
participant "GlobalHotkeyService\n(WM_HOTKEY)"      as GHK
participant "App.xaml.cs\n(HandleHotkey / wheel)"   as APP
participant "BrightnessFlyout\n.xaml.cs"            as BFL
participant "EnvironmentalCurveService\n(DispatcherTimer)" as ECS
participant "MonitorInfo\n(model)"                  as MI
participant "MonitorService"                        as MS
participant "AsyncThrottler<string>\n(latest-wins)" as TH
participant "DDCRecoveryService\n(event-triggered fallback worker;\ncandidates via\nGetStuckRecoveryCandidateIds)" as DRS
participant "KnownDisplaysStore\n(displays.json)"   as KDS
participant "DisplayService\n(IDisplayService)"     as DS
participant "Dxva2\n(P/Invoke)"                     as DXV
participant "App.RequestTrayRefresh"                as RTR
participant "TrayIconManager"                       as TIM

note over MS
  Single brightness backend - DDC/VCP (Dxva2 SetVCPFeature 0x10).
  No WMI / GammaRamp / internal-display fallback path exists.
end note

== Input source 1: slider drag ==
User -> BFL : Slider_PreviewMouseLeftButtonDown\n(track-click branch only)
loop while dragging (or scrubbing master)
  User -> BFL : Slider.ValueChanged TwoWay binding\n-> MonitorInfo.Brightness setter
  BFL -> MI  : Brightness = newVal
  MI  -> BFL : PropertyChanged (gated to integer transitions)
  BFL -> BFL : OnMonitorPropertyChanged\nApplyMasterToEnabledMonitors /\nUpdateMasterFromEnabledIndividuals\n(filter by IsParticipatingInMaster)
  MI  -> MS  : OnMonitorPropertyChanged\n(MonitorService is also subscribed)
  alt _hardwareWritesSuspendCount == 0
    MS -> MS : EnqueueDirectBrightness(monitor, RoundedBrightness)
  else suspended (curve owns hardware on startup restore)
    MS -> MS : skip - slider is pure visual state
  end
  BFL -> RTR : BrightnessUpdated event\n(via EffectiveRoundedBrightness)
  RTR -> TIM : Update(GetBrightnessAndTooltip)\n(UpdateCooldownMs cooldown)
end

== Input source 2: scroll wheel (flyout row or tray icon) ==
User -> BFL : MonitorGrid_PreviewMouseWheel
BFL -> BFL : DisengageCurveForUserAdjustment\n+ AdjustSliderByScrollDelta\n(slider.Value = clamp(...))
note right of BFL
  Tray-icon wheel goes through App.OnTrayWheel:
  for TrayWheelTarget.Brightness it writes
  m.Brightness directly on each monitor
  (same setter -> same MonitorService hook).
end note

== Input source 3: global hotkey ==
User -> GHK : Ctrl+Alt+...\n(WM_HOTKEY on message-only HWND)
GHK -> APP : Fired event (UI thread)
APP -> APP : HandleHotkey(action, parameter)
alt FullBright / FullDim
  APP -> APP : ApplyOrRestoreBrightness(target)\n-> m.Brightness = target
else IncrementMasterBrightness / DecrementMasterBrightness
  APP -> APP : AdjustAllMonitorBrightness(+/-HotkeyStep)\n-> m.Brightness = clamp(m.Brightness + delta)
end
APP -> MI : Brightness = newVal\n(routes through the slider-drag arrows above)
note right of APP
  Hotkey master/all/NL paths (App.xaml.cs:638-657,
  942-978) DO NOT call NotifyUserBrightnessAdjustment
  (distinct from the tray-scroll path which DOES).
  Master is gated out at MonitorService:1580 so master
  itself does not auto-release - but each enabled
  individual it propagates to falls through to the
  OnUserRelease auto-release at :1581 (H-05).
  Individual-row hotkeys: clean disengage via
  OnUserRelease + HarmonizeRow CR-preservation.
end note

== Input source 4: environmental curve evaluator ==
ECS -> ECS : Tick -> Evaluate()\nApplyBrightnessCurve(curve, t, smoothness, absolute)
note right of ECS
  Curve owns hardware; slider thumbs hold user's
  manual intent. Writes BYPASS the Brightness setter
  so the slider thumb does not drag along.
end note
loop for each MonitorInfo where SliderState == CurveActive
  ECS -> MI  : CurveTargetBrightness = absolute or (Brightness + offset)
  ECS -> MS  : EnqueueDirectBrightness(monitor, rowTargetPct)
end

== MonitorService write pipeline (shared by all sources) ==
MS -> TH  : RunAsync(entry.ID, ctx => DoBrightnessWriteAsync)\n(per-monitor key, latest-pending-wins)

note over TH
  AsyncThrottler<string> collapses bursts:
  while a payload runs, queued payloads
  collapse to "latest only" and inherit
  the WriteCooldownMs after the running one.
  Replacement signal short-circuits dwells via
  IThrottlerContext.HasReplacement.
end note

note over MS
  EnqueueDirectBrightness dedupes on
  entry.LastEnqueuedPercentage so a steady
  curve pct does not re-write every tick.
end note

TH -> MS  : DoBrightnessWriteAsync(entry, pct, ctx)
loop write attempts (ValidationAttempts, ScaledRetryDwellMs)
  MS -> DS  : TrySetVCPFeature(entry.DDC.BrightnessCode, raw)\nWithDDCLockAsync(per-monitor lock)
  DS -> DXV : SetVCPFeature
  DXV --> DS : ok / Win32 error
  DS  --> MS
  alt ok
  else transient I2C / monitor busy
    MS -> MS : Task.Delay(ScaledRetryDwellMs)\nbail if HasReplacement
  end
end

alt write succeeded and no replacement queued
  MS -> MS : VerifyAppliedAsync(entry, expectedRaw, ctx)
  loop verify attempts (ValidationAttempts)
    MS -> DS  : TryGetVCPFeature(entry.DDC.BrightnessCode)\nWithDDCLockAsync
    DS -> DXV : GetVCPFeatureAndVCPFeatureReply
    DXV --> DS
    DS  --> MS
    alt match (within +/- 1 raw unit)
    else mismatch -> RefreshHandle once + re-apply
      MS -> DS : TrySetVCPFeature(entry.DDC.BrightnessCode, raw)
    end
  end
else write retries exhausted, no replacement queued
  MS -> MS  : DemoteOnDDCFailure(entry, lastWriteError)\n(info.SliderState = SliderStateMachine.OnHardwareFailed();\n IsHardwareFunctional is derived from SliderState, not a setter;\n DDCRecoveryService picks the entry up via\n GetStuckRecoveryCandidateIds)
end

note over MS
  After every successful bus write, MonitorService stamps
  KnownDisplaysStore.LastBusBrightness for diagnostics/history.
  Acquisition no longer hydrates sliders from this value; it reads
  current DDC first, then profile/manual UI state is restored by
  BrightnessFlyout without implicit hardware replay.
end note
MS -> KDS : stamp LastBusBrightness

== Read paths (four sources) ==
note over MS
  DDC reads enter the throttler through four distinct paths:
   1. Initial/topology probe at MonitorService.Refresh / RefreshProbePhaseAsync
      (immediate on cold start; after the 1500 ms settle for recent topology events).
   2. Verify-after-write via VerifyAppliedAsync.
   3. Refresh re-probe of an existing row.
   4. Fallback acquisition pass via DDCRecoveryService calling MonitorService.Refresh.
end note

== DDC fallback acquisition ==
MS -> DRS : MonitorsRefreshed\ncandidate snapshot
alt failed/read-degraded known-DDC candidates exist
  DRS -> DRS : SignalDDCRecoveryNeeded()\n(single global flag)
  DRS -> DRS : start one worker if idle
  loop every 2 seconds while candidates remain
    DRS -> MS : Refresh()\nread-only acquisition path
    MS -> DS : TryGetVCPFeature(entry.DDC.BrightnessCode)\nvia RefreshProbePhaseAsync
    alt acquisition succeeds
      MS -> MS : PromoteRecovered / refresh promotion\nclears IsReadDegraded
      MS -> BFL : MonitorsAcquired(acquired rows)
    else acquisition still fails
      MS -> MS : keep Failed / ReadDegraded\nrefresh LastDDCError
    end
  end
else no candidates
  DRS -> DRS : ClearDDCRecoveryNeeded()\nworker exits
end

note right of DRS
  No per-monitor workers, no MaxRecoveryAttempts terminal state.
  Acquisition stays read-only; writes remain owned by
  MonitorsAcquired, curve, manual, and explicit user paths.
end note

note over MS
  Per-op timeouts inside WithDDCLockAsync.
  Cumulative deadline still NOT modeled -
  spurious timeouts remain possible on slow buses.
  Cascade guard: write/verify exhaustion DEFERS
  the demote when a fresher payload is queued.
end note

@enduml
